POV: Winter skincare needs extra care — but it doesn’t have to be complicated or expensive 💧

I used 5 affordable MCoBeauty skincare products to go from dry ➝ glowy in just a few simple steps ✨ 

Here’s my current glow-up routine:

1️⃣ Vitamin-C Rich Cleansing Butter – A luscious 3-in-1 facial cleanser, makeup remover, and hydrating mask that envelops your skin in moisture. I can’t get enough of the rich buttery texture 😍
2️⃣ Brightening Tonic Water – Contains Glycolic Acid to help exfoliate, brighten, and smooth your skin gently exfoliates and helps smooth texture
3️⃣ Glow Boost Vitamin C Serum – my dose of Vitamin C . It hydrates, brightens and revives tired winter skin. 
4️⃣ Intense Moisture Boost – a rich, yet lightweight cream that feels like a luscious  moisture hug for dry skin. 
5️⃣ Invisible Facial Sunscreen SPF50+ – provides ultra high UVA/UVB protection. It’s lightweight, no white cast, perfect as a primer before makeup. 

Simple, affordable, and effective! Products that deliver like high-end skin . I don’t think you can say no to that ! Perfect for mums like me who doesn’t have time for 10-step routines ♥️

Who says clean girl energy is just for Gen Z? These cute balms got a millennial mum like me feeling young and fresh again ✨ 

I am a typical Millennial mum… but also a sucker for clean, cute beauty like these super cute tinted Balmy Rose Lip Tints!!! 

Finally got my hands on these viral Balmy Rose Lip Potions by Alternative Stereo — and they’re just as dreamy as everyone says ✨
From the soft tint to the hydrating feel (and that packaging!!), I totally get the hype 💋

It’s great for mums coz of its hydrating and long lasting formula. It feels like light whipped cream on the lips . 

Available now at our fave Asian beauty destination, W Cosmetics ! They literally have an entire stand dedicated to Alternative Stereo !
